ZH: 他太肥了，需要减肥。
EN: He is too fat and needs to lose weight.

ZH: 这只猪太肥了，一定是天天吃东西。
EN: This pig is too fat, it must eat all day long.

ZH: 午饭后不要吃太多甜食，容易长得太肥。
EN: Don't eat too many sweets after lunch, it's easy to get too fat.

ZH: 这只狗很肥，看来主人有给他喂好吃的。
EN: This dog is very fat, looks like the owner feeds it well.

ZH: 他的脸庞看起来有些肥胖。
EN: His face looks a bit chubby.

ZH: 我觉得我的肚子有点肥了，该节食了。
EN: I feel like my belly is getting fat, I should diet.

ZH: 光吃不运动容易变肥。
EN: Just eating and not exercising will make you fat.

ZH: 肥肉不但影响外貌，也不好健康。
EN: Fat not only affects appearance, but also health.

ZH: 她的风格是穿肥大的衣服。
EN: Her style is wearing oversized clothes.

ZH: 肥大的服装不适合每个人。
EN: Baggy clothes don't suit everyone.

ZH: 他买了一条肥大的围巾来御寒。
EN: He bought a large scarf to keep warm.

ZH: 她的房间里有很多肥大的沙发。
EN: There are many bulky sofas in her room.

ZH: 这只猫伸了一个肥大的懒腰。
EN: The cat stretched out a big yawn.

ZH: 这款皮包设计得非常肥大。
EN: This leather bag is designed very bulky.

ZH: 我的个子太矮了，肥大的衣服显得我更矮。
EN: I'm too short, bulky clothes make me look even shorter.

ZH: 现在流行的裤子比以前的要宽肥。
EN: The pants that are popular now are wider and bulkier than before.

ZH: 女生也可以穿肥大的外套，很有型。
EN: Girls can also wear oversized jackets, very stylish.

ZH: 肥肉是胖的主要原因之一。
EN: Fat is one of the main causes of obesity.

ZH: 他的双下巴有点肥胖。
EN: His double chin is a bit chubby.
